License interaction with Kilolock
-----------------------------------

Kilolock itself is licensed under Apache-2.0 (see ../../LICENSE).
Apache-2.0 and MPL-2.0 are compatible at the file level: each vendored
file remains under MPL-2.0; Kilolock's own code (everything outside
this directory) is Apache-2.0. Distributing Kilolock distributes
these MPL-2.0 files; that distribution complies with MPL-2.0 because
the files retain their license headers and are not modified.

Maintenance
-----------

The protocol files are regenerated upstream from .proto sources using
protoc + protoc-gen-go + protoc-gen-go-grpc. We do not regenerate them
locally; we copy the generated artifacts from a tagged release of
terraform-plugin-go. To bump:

  1. Pick a new terraform-plugin-go tag (e.g. v0.32.0).
  2. Re-download all six files from that tag.
  3. Update the version string in this NOTICE.
  4. Run `go test -tags=integration ./internal/provider/...` against
     real provider binaries to confirm the protocol surface still works.

We intentionally do not run protoc ourselves; doing so would require
toolchain version-pinning and add no value over taking the official
generated artifacts.
